  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "k71tqZuounEKOB6iwRxrENwNto4=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:31.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "Collaboration adds per-user op feeds on top of the single-user sync \u2014 and the additional storage cost is small and structural rather than full re-duplication:\n\n**Already present (single-user baseline)**\n- PGlite: all operations (local + remote)\n- Swarm /bytes: operation batches (per user)\n- Single-user feeds: doc/drive/user manifests (personal backup)\n\n**New in collaboration**\n- Collab index feed: 1 per shared document (~1 KB)\n- Per-user op feeds: 1 per user per document\n  - Content: `SyncEnvelope` wrapping the SAME operations that are already in the single-user /bytes batches\n\n**What's actually added**:\n- Feed pointer updates: ~64 bytes per update per user\n- SyncEnvelope wrappers around operations (OperationContext metadata)\n\n**Overhead quantified**: ~20% per op for the context metadata. The core action data itself is not duplicated \u2014 only the wrapping envelope.\n\n**Why it matters**: this means collaboration scales linearly in users rather than in users x ops. Adding N collaborators to a document doesn't N-duplicate the ops; it adds N small-wrapped pointers over the same underlying content-addressed operation chunks.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:31.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:31.000Z"
    }
  },
